Class ArrayDoubleStack

  • java.lang.Object
    • impl.ArrayDoubleStack
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDoubleStack
    public class ArrayDoubleStack
extends java.lang.Object
implements IDoubleStack
    Implements a single array of a given size to create two equally sized stacks.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor Description
      ArrayDoubleStack​(int maxSize)
      Constructor creates an array of a given size and then sets the two stacks sizes to an equal even number.

    • Constructor Detail

      • ArrayDoubleStack

        public ArrayDoubleStack​(int maxSize)
        Constructor creates an array of a given size and then sets the two stacks sizes to an equal even number.
        Parameters:
        maxSize - The total size of the underlying array. This is divided into two evenly sized stacks. "Odd" values will be decremented to prevent erroneous array slots.
